 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The artificial intelligences are getting smarter. </p=
><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>On Tuesday, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com=
/redirect/eda0c9fb-afbe-456d-bf31-6033d6d06c46?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5=
T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; text-decoration: underline;">Meta released Llama 3.1 405B</a><span>, a mo=
nster 405 billion parameter model trained on over 15 trillion tokens using =
16,000 NVIDIA H100 GPUs. The elegantly-named Llama 3.1 405B is competitive =
with best-in-class closed-source models from companies like OpenAI and Anth=
ropic, coming in first in Instruction Following and second in Math (behind =
Claude 3.5 Sonnet and ahead of GPT-4o) according to </span><a href=3D"https=
://substack.com/redirect/f4a2f1f9-ab67-498c-97e4-104d14bda08b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: =
rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Scale&#8217;s SEAL Leaderboar=
ds</a><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>As expected, they open sour=
ced the whole thing. Along with the release, Zuck penned a letter titled </=
span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/b352b22a-ef74-4262-93e5-5=
db0807edb32?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Open=
 Source is the Path Forward</a><span>, </span></em><span>in which he makes =
the case that open source is good for developers, for Meta, and for the wor=
ld. Of note, he calls out Apple:</span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left=
: 4px solid #0c2427; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-l=
eft: 20px;"><em>One of my formative experiences has been building our servi=
ces constrained by what Apple will let us build on their platforms. Between=
 the way they tax developers, the arbitrary rules they apply, and all the p=
roduct innovations they block from shipping, it&#8217;s clear that Meta and=
 many other companies would be freed up to build much better services for p=
eople if we could build the best versions of our products and competitors w=
ere not able to constrain what we could build.</em></p></blockquote><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">And he argues that open models are both safer against unintentio=
nal harm, because they&#8217;ll have more eyes on them, and intentional har=
m, because China is probably stealing the closed model weights anyway. Zuck=
 is really coming into his own. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>On Wednesday, M=
istral released </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/28d413ba-9f=
80-4157-9bb4-f52e1a849fab?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: un=
derline;">Mistral Large 2</a><span>, which it says beats Llama 3.1 405B on =
Coding and Math with just 123 billion parameters. The Scale SEAL Leaderboar=
d has yet to be updated, but in either case, we have some powerful open mod=
els to work with. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Then yesterday, the closed m=
odels came roaring back. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Yesterday morning, Goo=
gle Deepmind announced that its Alpha Proof and AlphaGeometry 2 models </sp=
an><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/cf6b3317-0f49-470c-86f6-43eb711=
c57ba?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" r=
el style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">achieved s=
ilver-medal standard solving International Mathematical Olympiad problems</=
a><span>. I continue to think that while Google&#8217;s consumer-facing AI =
products have been hilariously poorly executed, the company keeps pumping o=
ut some of the coolest and most useful results in categories like bio and n=
ow math. The IMO &#8220;is the largest and most prestigious competition for=
 young mathematicians, held annually since 1959,&#8221; and it&#8217;s real=
ly hard. AI struggles with really simple math occasionally, so this seems l=
ike a big breakthrough, and one step closer to using AI to help solve the r=
eally big problems. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And finally, yesterd=
ay afternoon, OpenAI, not to be left out, shared </span><a href=3D"https://=
substack.com/redirect/7b9a91e3-4bf3-4cfe-b099-7b4db7bca712?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">SearchGPT</a><span>, which is an=
 AI-powered search engine that looks a lot like </span><a href=3D"https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/23f13e08-4763-4ce3-9818-6282b4d54fdc?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Perplexity</a><span>. Sam Altman =
also </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/12cce889-bba6-4625-a3a=
7-3f059149a222?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">t=
weeted</a><span> that the company will begin rolling out alpha rollouts of =
its voice product next week. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s intere=
sting to see the big foundation model companies carving out slightly differ=
ent niches on models that seem to perform roughly at the same level: OpenAI=
 is focused on product (although I can&#8217;t wait to see GPT-5), Anthropi=
c is focused on product as well, bringing more into my favorite model (Clau=
de 3.5 Sonnet), Meta and Mistral are focused on open source, and Google Dee=
pmind is focused on really hard math and science problems. </p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;">Bring on the competition. I&#8217;m trying to hang out with Dan in It=
aly while the AIs do my job. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>(3)</strong><spa=
