 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In the midst of all the new releases, researchers pub=
lished a paper in </span><em>Nature</em><span> showing that the more AI-gen=
erated data models are trained on, the worse they perform. </span></p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">Here&#8217;s the argument. Current LLMs are trained on data mo=
stly created by humans.As LLMs become more common, they'll start generating=
 a lot of content that ends up on the internet. Future LLMs might then be t=
rained on data that includes a mix of human-created and AI-generated conten=
t. The researchers found that when this happens repeatedly (they call it &q=
uot;learning with generational data&quot;), the AI models start to lose som=
e important information about the original, human-created data. They call t=
his problem &quot;model collapse.&quot;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Model collapse=
 happens in two stages: </p><ul style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li st=
yle=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-s=
izing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Early stage:</=
strong><span> The AI forgets about rare or uncommon things in the data.</sp=
an></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"=
><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><str=
ong>Late stage:</strong><span> The AI's outputs become less varied and more=
 repetitive.</span></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Researchers are smart an=
d there&#8217;s a lot of money on the line, so I&#8217;m sure that in each =
of the labs there are already developments underway to get around the data =
wall that doesn&#8217;t simply involve dumping AI-generated content into tr=
aining sets, but I read this as another sign that we won&#8217;t see a &#82=
20;fast takeoff&#8221; in which AI gets so smart, powerful, and humanlike s=
o quickly that we don&#8217;t have time to react and are all useless pets. =
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
